I have created a simple program to demonstrate what I think is an error in the 
formatting of the layout for source filename and line number, (%F:%L).


package com.test;

import org.apache.log4j.*;

public class LogTest {
    static Category log = Category.getInstance 
"com.axaim.repair_station.notify");

  	public static void main(String[] args) {
		if (args.length != 1)
		{
			System.out.println ("Usage java LogTest 'log config 
file'");
			System.exit(1);
		}

  		// Set the logging mechanism properties
		PropertyConfigurator.configure(args[0]);
		log.info ("Before loop");
// 		Uncomment the lines below and re-build. This will cause output 
// of source filename and line numbers to become ?:?
//		for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++)
//		{
//			log.debug ("In loop" + i);
//		}
//
		log.info ("After loop");
  	}
}



When the program is built wihtout the loop, I get the following output in my 
log,

  2001-01-10 15:45:20,896 [main ] INFO  (LogTest.java:23) - Before loop
  2001-01-10 15:45:20,896 [main ] INFO  (LogTest.java:30) - After loop

When the is uncommented and the java re-built I get built ...

  2001-01-10 18:01:25,613 [main ] INFO  (?:?) - Before loop
  2001-01-10 18:01:25,613 [main ] DEBUG (?:?) - In loop0
  2001-01-10 18:01:25,629 [main ] DEBUG (?:?) - In loop1
  2001-01-10 18:01:25,629 [main ] INFO  (?:?) - After loop

The config file that I used is shgown below,

log4j.rootCategory=DEBUG, stdout
log4j.appender.stdout=org.apache.log4j.FileAppender
log4j.appender.stdout.File=System.out  
log4j.appender.stdout.layout=org.apache.log4j.PatternLayout  
log4j.appender.stdout.layout.ConversionPattern=%d [%t] %-5p (%F:%L) %c - %m%n  

Its the first time I have used this so the mistake could easily be on my part. 

If you do find out anything please let me know,

Many thanks,

Richard

ps It also happened in the previous release 0.91
